< text>
I was looking for a new place to reward myself with a massage. I visited Elememts Massage to try this facility out.  I have been back 3x and each time the service is great. They call you the day before to remind you of the appointment, (you can cancel as late as 7pm the day before your appointment) the facility is clean and the massage room is adequatey sized. They offer a hanger and clothes basket to place items in, along with an andes mint :)
My female masseuse that I've had is very professional, friendly and provides the right pressure in those tension spots, without making me sore the next day.
They also have a monthly program if you want to join and they will give you a discount on the massage price. They also provide aromotherapy and hot stone massages too.  I'm have been very pleased with the service I receive here.< /text>

<time>1614449516154</time><pictures>None<//pictures><response>None<//response><name>buggs R<//name>< Review>
I was never a supercuts fan, but here I am writing this review.

Before me coming here, I would go to my local barbershop. Here are a couple of reasons why I switched over.

1. Long waiting line even up to 2hrs to get a haircut, although you called to book an appointment.
2. They only take cash, which is a hassle to waste time at the bank.
3. Some barbers like yapping instead of getting down to business and just cut hair.

Those are a couple of reasons why I come to Supercuts. They get down to business and charge around 20 bucks. At least at this location, when I book an appointment, I don't have to wait to get a haircut, but the most beautiful part of this is they accept debit cards which is a massive advantage for people like myself that hate wasting time at the ATMs.

I hope this helps persuade you, have a fantastic day!< /Review>

Sure enough, a couple months later we receive a letter in the mail from a collection agency ‚Äî repeat, a collection agency ‚Äî saying Keep Truckin‚Äô filed a claim against us. Turns out, their ELD boxes are leased to our company on an agreement (news to us ‚Äî they‚Äôve been collecting dust in our garage for the last six months and we‚Äôd gladly return them), but instead of Keep Truckin‚Äô clearly communicating this to us, especially as we are canceling our contract, they chose to stay silent and wait. Then, when our credit card number was no longer valid, decided to submit our bill to a collection agency for a total lease price of more than the ELDs are worth, dragging our company name through the mud in the process. There was no warning, no phone call, no email (even though that was their excuse... ‚ÄúDid you get our email?‚Äù) and especially, no manners. By the way things unfolded it seems like this is their standard business model: stay silent until the former customer trashes the ELDs, then charge them for it ‚Äî a nice way to boost the bottom line.

He spent a couple of minutes looking into the panels. First question to me was ‚ÄúDo you like fire?‚Äù I said ‚ÄúNO‚Äù. He said ‚Äúthen, you got big problem‚Äù. He gave me 2 options, the cheap way was for him to redo the wirings to the compressor, total cost $1060 BUT will not guarantee it will solve the problem. The second option was to replace the compressor, total cost $5000, that‚Äôs right, $5000. I respectfully declined both and paid the ‚Äúdiagnostic‚Äù fee.
Called an independent tech (his own boss). He came out the next day. It turned out the contactor relay needed to be replaced. He left and came back within an hour with the new part. < Review>
NexGen called me to alert me to the  free service I had coming on the two systems we installed last April, and wanted to make sure I scheduled it before the 1 year period ran out.  I had actually forgotten we had this benefit so I definitely appreciated the follow-up call.  Andy, their Tech, came out (on time) and went over the service with me and asked if I had any questions or would like him to perform anything special on the system.  I DID want to check the balancing and be sure about which units were operating which thermostats.  We had a thermostat, and return ducts and controllable venting installed for each of the 3 bedrooms, in addition to the two new thermostats controlling (1) the master bedroom and 2(2) the family room/ kitchen living area.  All thermostats can be remotely controlled with the Honeywell iPhone app, which is a real plus when returning from a trip and you want to have the house cooled down before you arrive.  Andy checked the entire system's ductwork in the attic and the compressor units outside and mad adjustments that I asked him to on the airflow in the master bedroom and bathroom.  He even gave me a chart the he drew up for me letting me know which thermostats (6) are operating on which of the 2 systems.  Our system required heavy duty filters and Andy doesn't normally carry that size (5" thick) in his truck, so he went to the supply house and picked them up, and came right back and finished up the service call.  Andy covered all of my questions and adjusted the system at no charge on his routine service call.
NexGen, and ALL of their Tech's (like Andy) are extremely professional and knowledgeable; and very well trained on providing exceptional customer service.  I would recommend them to ANYONE looking to repair or update their heating and air conditioning systems.  We spent a considerable amount of money replacing bot systems, plus adding a garage unit, but it has been worth every penny of the investment and the service has been beyond what we expected.< /Review>

<Rate>5<//Rate>< Text>
After 16 years in our house (home is 25 years old) time to get a quote on replacing our leaking HVAC unit, typed in for a A/C and Heating company in Googled it and the company NexGen was at the top of the list. They quoted a service call quote and would apply that to the replacement price if we decided to purchase it. We asked for a sale technician to give a free estimate for a new unit, a very pleasant phone conversation  led to sending out a salesman for a 9:00am appointment, which he (David) arrived at the scheduled time. We spent time getting to know one another and was very impressed with his years experience and knowledge of the Industry and his competitors. He inspected our unit and explained everything that was to be done. Just as he was going to install it himself, he explained why he recommended out of the 3 different products, Lennox, Trane and Daikin, we chose the Daikin brand, which is the Goodman company out of Texas, Lifetime warranty, Hi-Efficiency, competitively priced, (estimates from last year where higher than his quote for this year, also, after our lengthy questions and answers,  3 hours later, we decided to go with the estimate,  realizing the expense we where going to go thru,  the salesman offered his company to buy the interest down that was better than our credit union with no money down and an affordable monthly payment, with a transferable warranty.
He also said he could have a crew of 4 this afternoon to tear out the old heater and A/C unit and once we decided to go with his company, he made a phone call 1/2 hour later 2 vans from NexGen showed up knocking on our door, talk about service, The crew got started at 12:00 removed and replace the system by 5:00 and the next morning another crew in 2 nice  NexGen  vans arrived at the time they where scheduled. t           This crew did all the equipment hook up electrical and finished rebuilding sheet metal work and insulating the attic, Wifi Thermostat installed. all was completed in 8 hours, cleaned up like no one was there. They all wore booties on there work shoes and covered the floors with canvas.
I give NexGen a 5 star out of 5, personality, professionalism, even the installers are very courteous and enjoy the company they work for. I've been in sales, manufacturing, retail and wholesale over 50 years and retired 1 1/2 years, at 75 its nice to know there is a company like NexGen to service customers the old fashion way, a pleasant voice, a smile and a handshake with your employees saying, thank you for you business.
I wanted to acknowledge all the men that did the work at my house, names where mentioned and wanted to give them recognition for a job well done, all of them where busy from removing the old heater and A/C to the crew that came out and finished the job, a job well done.
From the project manager David (salesman), Gustavo, Omar, Albert, Arturo. This was the second crew that finished up the installation the next  day. The 1st crew where in the area from Palm Springs, did the removal and installation, I don't remember their names, please thank them.</Text>

<Review>Saturday morning veggie and fruit market with good selection of standard, asian, Indian, south east asian veggies. Was able to find some unique items like methi (fenugreek leaves), arbi, karela (bitter gourd), saag (mustard greens), etc. One of the stalls is family run (Lee farms) and will do special orders if you ask them in advance. I was able to get a large batch of full lemongrass plants and leaves. Only one of the stalls is certified organic and has a wide range of vegetables. Fresh egg vendor, a couple stalls that sell small plants and orchids, and one stall that sells local honey. Great spot to get seasonal fresh items. Check it out!</Review><Pics>None<//Pics><Resp>None</Resp>< Gmap_id>

<Review>Not a good location. I prefer the Hanford location as they are consistent with how they make their food and the service in Hanford is much better. Tonight just a bunch of kids just standing around and talking were working tonight. As someone had pointed out in another review, if there's an older gentleman working the food tastes better as for the younger people working it wasn't good. Tonight I happened to have the younger people. I ordered the steak special and the steak had more tough bits in it this time. I've only been to this location once this being that only visit but in Hanford I never had an issue with the steak at all. Overall I think I will stick to the one in Hanford and I'll pass on this location. If it's a hit or miss like this everytime it's not really worth going back to in my opinion. Having grown up in Hanford, I used to frequent Boston's a lot so I knew what i was getting everytime but this location or the employees working tonight couldn't keep up with what the folks in Hanford are doing. This is my treat I get everytime I come back to visit family and friends but sadly I was disappointed this time around. I don't recommend this location if all of the kids are working. For those who are passing through the valley and may still consider eating here; the popular items from this restaurant are the chicken kabob salads, the steak special sandwich (basically a cheesesteak) and the garlic bread which is a cheese bread made with locally made sandwich bread from Basque; the same as the one used for the steak special. So it's the sandwich bread topped with what the restaurant calls mayo or I call it 'garlic aioli' call it whatever you want, finally topped off with their pizza cheese. It's a very simple garlic bread but it's very tasty. Those are their specialty along with their pizza which all of them are pretty good. They cut their pizzas into squares so that's a pretty unique thing about this place too.<//Review><Pics>None<//Pics><Resp>None</Resp>< gmapID>

< user_name>
Jared Foster< /user_name>
<date>1539744498947<//date><Rate>2<//Rate><review>The Boston House of Pizza has some problems, but they are problems that can be easily fixed. Upon entering the store front, one can't help but notice the horrible decor. The decor actually proved to be a distraction from the meal. However, the acoustics are good. The place was about half full, but conversation was not drowned out by other patrons.
I ordered a calzone with sausage, meatball, olives, mushrooms, and minced garlic. My friend had a pie with chicken, sausage, and meatballs. The chicken was quite dry and tough to swallow, as was the crust on my calzone. The crust was cooked properly though, and had the right crisp on the bottom. The mushrooms were right out of a can and devoid of any flavor that should have been present with sausage and marinara sauce.
Speaking of sauce, it is basically ketchup with a little dry oregeno sprinkled in. The sausage (where found) was good, had proper fennel flavor.
The calzone was topped with cheese. While this helped the crust go down, it was way too much cheese for the little amount of other flavors. It was served with the flimsiest plastic wear that broke before I could finish the meal.
In general, my impression is that this place used to be a great, a little gem in an otherwise small town in the San Jaoquin Valley. It probably built up a loyal, local following over many years of great service and food. But, they let their standards fall by the wayside, and now can't afford to bring it back up to their former standards. This is evidenced by the missing 'B' on the front marquis sign and the dark arcade games near the bathrooms. It is kind of a shame, actually. Towns like this need a shining place to meet family and friends. I suppose though, to be fair, I will give it 2 stars because it was good enough to take back to the hotel room for tomorrow.< /review><Pics>[{'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipOJmWcw_xLCkLRg_QdPZmM2uBUDc3rnTKT0ufV7=w150-h150-k-no-p']}]< /Pics>< Resp>

<Rating>5< /Rating><Text>We've been in Lemoore for 20 years. It was the first pizza place we tried and is still our go to restaurant for pizza and sub sandwiches. I just don't get the other chain pizza parlors in town. There's no comparison to Boston.
As for the service I don't get whoat others have said about their bad experience. Yes sometimes we wait a bit but maybe I'm on small town time. We don't feel the need to be in a hurry. No they are not overly friendly but they are normally busy with no time for small talk. And they have never been rude to me. The interior was remodeled a few years ago and is tastefully done with a cool tin ceiling and stained glass pendant lights over the tables. Oh... and the "area" is not a bad neighborhood!  I feel very safe when I go to pick up food. The parking could be better but it is what it is.
Pizzas are good. Especially the Boston Special. Chef salad is great with little pinwheels of meat and cheese. I love the Steak sandwich  The meat is so tender.

< Text>
The site is impeccably clean, and the staff is courteous and helpful. The building is new, and access is convenient. My one main complaint is the payment system, not about this location itself. Instead of having a payment portal on the website, they send you a payment link via text. If you are late, which I have due to job loss because of the pandemic, you have to go into the office to make a payment. I don't know any businesses that still operate like this, especially when we are trying to reduce in-person contact. I had to make several calls to escalate this issue, then sign and fax a form to get permission to pay over the phone...in 2020. StorQuest really needs to update its payment system.</Text>
